During the Reagan and Clinton presidencies, the welfare system in the
U.S. was in a shambles and it became a priority for reform.

Changes proposed included time limits on welfare checks and a
requirement that welfare recipients work if able.

Other capitalist nations also faced a need for welfare reform.</SUM>
